20/03/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Aleksandar Dzombic and his visiting Serbian counterpart Mirko Cvetkovic assessed on Friday (March 18th) that relations between Banja Luka and Belgrade are excellent. The two leaders signed bilateral agreements on energy, transport, infrastructure and science during the joint session of the governments of RS and Serbia. The next joint governmental session reportedly will be held in Belgrade. (Tanjug, Blic, B92 - 18/03/11)
